caption: Excellent 四川 food!! I feel like I'm back in 重庆!! Authentic and genuine,  great for take out during these crazy times.  Try something you haven't had,  you'll love it!
Dongpo Impression is my favorite restaurant! The lady running this place is so kind-hearted and always gives you extra dishes! I can’t recommend Dongpo Impression enough!
Highly recommend! Authentic Szechuan food. Yummy and services are friendly. Will come over again!

She had the spicy chicken potato noodle (her favorite) while I had Zhong’s Dumplings with tofu and seafood soup!  Their delivery person was very good handling the food. Everything came perfectly wrapped and securely packaged. Will continue to order delivery from them. Also order enough and they might toss you an appetizer or side on the house! Tip well!

The lady that manages the restaurant is amazing and has warm personality! She works as both waitress and bus lady. The food is DELICIOUS. Me and several patients at the clinic I work (right across the street) have all agreed that we love their Sichuan Chicken Stew!

Dong Po has wonderful Szechuan style food : spicy, tasty, juicy. I am always impressed by their hospitality. I especially love their spicy Chicken Noodle Stew and their awesome ice jelly desert with syrup!

I ordered Beef Maw Blood Cake & Spicy Tofu and Eel Pot. Both of them are terrible!!!! The blood is not fresh. It tastes really bad! Even worse, the thing in the 2nd dish is not eel at all. It has a strange taste of raw fishes, which is truly bad. I am so disappointed. And the two dishes are also kind of pricy, especially the eel is about $25 but taste awful!!!

I came here with a friend thinking we might be able to find Hangzhou cuisine but found mainly Szechuan food, which was still tasty, and would be my recommended food items here. Stick with the spicy!  We got the spicy wontons, water spinach, Dongpo pork belly, and Dongpo fish. The wontons was the most well-made. The fish tasted fresh but the pork was a bit greasy and lacking flavor imo. Veggies were great. The portions were quite large and we ended up taking a lot of food home, however, the bill came out to be a lot pricier than expected.  Service was quite slow since there were a couple of other customers, and only one server (the lady was suuuper nice). We had to wait for quite some time for our food to come and to get the check. I also felt awkward speaking during the meal because it was so quiet in the restaurant. Not anyone's fault--the other customers just happened to not talk.  I think the food here is okay, and the menu items are hit or miss. The restaurant is a tiny bit out of the way of most Chinatown restaurants.

The table service was excellent here, as it was very friendly and comforting. Unfortunately, the food did not live up to my expectations of a restaurant specializing in Sichuan cuisine.  I had the boiled fish, twice cooked pork, and Dan Dan Noodle. The quality was average and the taste being merely authentic. I felt each dish was very underwhelming for a Sichuan dish, as it lacked spiciness, but mostly the complexity of spices that remains to be a signature of Sichuan cuisine.  The Dan Dan Noodle was the most underwhelming because it reminded me more of beef lo mein than Dan Dan Noodle. It was served with one tbsp of beef and some sauce at the bottom, nothing else. Other than that, the food is average and moderately priced for a quick bite with larger parties.

(Translated by Google) The interior is shabby but the restaurant is basic. Sell ​​a variety of Sichuan cuisine. There are so many menus that you can choose bokbulbok bokbulbok, but if you choose to eat at a typical Chinese restaurant, don't be disappointed. But the price is a little expensive. Among the nearby Sichuan restaurants, it is said to suit the taste of locals.  (Original) 인테리어는 초라하지만 기본은 있는 식당. 다양한 사천 지역의 요리들을 판매한다. 메뉴가 너무 많아서 살짝 고를 때 복불복이지만 일반 중국식당에서 먹는 메뉴를 고르면 실망할 일은 없다. 하지만, 가격이 살짝 비싸다는게 흠. 근처의 사천 식당 중에서는 현지인들의 입맛에 잘 맞는 편이라고 한다.
The service was excellent and there is always a smiley face. The food was excellent and authentic. It definitely deserves more credit and customer than it seems.

Great authentic spicy Szechuan food. Food tastes good and is pretty cheap. Feels a bit like a hole in the wall since it's not on the two main roads of Chinatown but definitely worth a try. The interior is pretty basic but staff are nice. Food comes out quickly and tastes good and that's what we're here for!
The food was hot and delicious.  I can't wait to get back to try more for m the menu.  The grilled tilapia was goodness.

Kind, attentive service. The food was good and plentiful, even if prices were higher than those in other restaurants on Wentworth St. and in Chinatown Square. However, they offer 2 free little appetizers (peanuts and bamboo salad, I think?) while you look at the menu, plus a free pot of tea. The Kung Pao Chicken was nice, no Panda Express-style dish. It had plenty of celery, chicken, peanuts and hot red peppers nicely prepared and cooked. You could taste the garlic and the ginger in the sauce. I also ordered a cucumber salad, which was delicious and prepared with an entire cucumber. Portions are not skimpy, which is greatly appreciated. The decor and ambiance of the place are a little outdated, definitely not as hip as the rest of the restaurants around in Chinatown, but I believe this place is worth a try.

This is authentic Chinese food. My husband and I were able to order "Fu Zhu" a tofu salad that wasn't on the menu we used to enjoy in China. The nice woman also gave us a desert.  If you relax your standards and step outside your comfort zone you will be treated to real Chinese food, not American Chinese food.
Wonderful food! Meizhou chili chicken and Mongolian beef were excellent.
This is a fantastic restaurant hidden in a not so ideal location, therefore the service is not great and not much customers around, but what can I say, I love the taste.
I think the main cheif was not there that day or something
This chicken stew is sooo good! Very authentic Sichuan skewers! CHuan Chuan
Authentic Sichuan. Staff was extremely friendly. Food was great. Felt like I was back in China again. Will be back.
great food great service

I have no idea how there are all these negative reviews. Super authentic, delicious Sichuan food. Maybe the people with negative reviews just don’t like real Sichuan food? The Dan Dan was some of the best I had. Extremely friendly staff. Will go back many more times

(Translated by Google) I chose this place for my first meal in Chicago. I was surprised that the United States can have such authentic Sichuan food. I will return to China tomorrow and chose this place for my last meal. There is actually ice powder. Mapo tofu tastes better than many restaurants in Chengdu. And this rib is good  (Original) 到芝加哥的第一餐选择了这里，意外惊喜美国能有这么地道的川菜，明天回国，最后一餐又选择了这里，居然还有冰粉，麻婆豆腐比成都好多餐厅的味道都好吃。还有这个排骨不错

This place changed names and got even better! The staff was incredibly attentive and friendly. Everything we ate was beautifully prepared and seasoned, ask about their off-menu specials ;)  Perfect for dates, hanging out. Their BYOB policy, great prices, excellent hot pot (in literally any other weather but a Chicago heat wave!)  Come see the new Chinatown!
Was in China a month ago and ate very similar food! Great flavor! Amazing service!
Very authentic. Good spice. Great flavors. Felt like I was back in China. The service was wonderful, too.

Authentic Sichuan food in ample portions. Unless you're feeling especially ravenous, one entree is likely enough for two people.
Sichuan food that will blow your mind. This place is authentic, the real deal. Avoid all the other bleh Cantonese restaurants, come here for some actual good Chinese food.
Best Sichuan restaurant in Chicago! Authentic, DELICIOUS taste (chef is from Sichuan), generous portions, plus the friendly staff, there’s no better choice when in Chinatown!

Great food, great price

Get the EGGPLANT.
Good food,  OK atmosphere.

Very great food! Came from Toronto to visit family and was recommended to this place. Having grown up in Sichuan and with access to plenty of Sichuan food in Toronto, I can say the taste is definitely authentic! If you are looking for spicy and authentic Sichuan food, this is it. If you looking for more western styled Szechuan food, maybe look elsewhere.

For anyone that has ever lived in Sichuan province this is as close as you are going to get to authentic in Chicago. Every bite takes me back to my time in Chengdu. The Ybin cold noodles, pork dumplings, and salted chicken pot are the must eats. Service is also friendly and BYOB is always awesome. Great place to go with friends :)
I keep going back- definitely one of Chinatown's best.

This restaurant specializes in the cuisine of zigong, sichuan's third largest city (after Chengdu and Chongqing). All the usual favorites are here, as well as unexpected dishes I've never seen anywhere else. This place really showcases how much depth there is in Sichuan cuisine. The flavors are super clean, and have a lot if pop. This is by far and away the best Sichuan food in the city. There's really nothing close in quality, even Lao Szechuan pales in comparison.
The food here is great.  My absolute favorite chinese dish is from here, Salt merchants chicken! It's spicy so make sure you order the right amount of spice
Solid food, reasonable price, friendly service. I ve been here numerous times and it's been consistently delicious.
Enjoy the environment and food .
Quite tasty! Every dish we ordered was exquisite. Free parking and great service.
I love this place: the good, the ppl, and many more ...

Anyone who doesn't love this place is a clueless gringo.  I recommend the spicy beef noodle, the tea-smoked duck, and the salt miner's eggplant. Try to come a few hours before closing, before the chef gets too tired.
Authentic Chinese!
The food is great, the environment is totally elegant Chinese style and the price is quite reasonable! I strongly recommend here!!

This is by far my favorite place in Chinatown -- truly authentic Sichuan.  Great food, comfortable atmosphere, pleasant waitstaff, inexpensive.  Order the crunchy garlic shrimp with noodles!  Also, Double Li's is flexible and fun -- when my brother came back to the states after 6 months in China he was able to practice his Mandarin and order an item off the menu!
Very non-western meals available here, including bone-in frog cubes and lamb cooked in it's on blood. If you can get past the concept of the food, it's pretty delicious.
